Name: developmental disorder of mental health
Definition: A disease of mental health that occur during a child's developmental period between birth and age 18 resulting in retarding of the child's psychological or physical development.

Name: sexual disorder
Definition: A disease of mental health that involves the impairment in normal sexual functioning.

Name: dissociative disorder
Definition: A disease of mental health in which the normally well-integrated functions of memory

Name: impulse control disorder
Definition: A disease of mental health that involves a failure to resist an impulsive act or behaviour that may be harmful to self or others.

Name: gender identity disorder
Definition: A disease of mental health that involves a conflict between a person's actual physical gender and the gender that person identifies himself or herself as.

Name: personality disorder
Definition: A disease of mental health that involve long-term patterns of thoughts and behaviors that cause serious problems with relationships and work.

Name: obsolete residual schizophrenia chronic state with acute exacerbation
Definition: A disease of mental health that involve long-term patterns of thoughts and behaviors that cause serious problems with relationships and work.

Name: cognitive disorder
Definition: A disease of mental health that affects cognitive functions including memory processing

Name: factitious disorder
Definition: A disease of mental health where symptoms are deliberately produced

Name: substance-related disorder
Definition: A disease of mental health involving the abuse or dependence on a substance that is ingested in order to produce a high

Name: somatoform disorder
Definition: A disease of mental health that involves physical symptoms suggesting a physical illness where the biological or medical cause of the symptoms is indeterminate.

Name: obsolete Iris or ciliary body disorder
Definition: A disease of mental health that involves physical symptoms suggesting a physical illness where the biological or medical cause of the symptoms is indeterminate.

Name: adjustment disorder
Definition: A disease of mental health that is an abnormal and excessive emotional and behavioral reaction to a life stress that develops within 3 months of a life stress

Name: obsolete neoplasm of body of uterus
Definition: A disease of mental health that is an abnormal and excessive emotional and behavioral reaction to a life stress that develops within 3 months of a life stress

Name: obsolete central nervous system soft tissue neoplasm
Definition: A disease of mental health that is an abnormal and excessive emotional and behavioral reaction to a life stress that develops within 3 months of a life stress
Synonym: soft tissue tumor of the CNS

Name: obsolete meninges gliomatosis
Definition: A disease of mental health that is an abnormal and excessive emotional and behavioral reaction to a life stress that develops within 3 months of a life stress

Name: obsolete malignant neoplasm of meninges
Definition: A disease of mental health that is an abnormal and excessive emotional and behavioral reaction to a life stress that develops within 3 months of a life stress

Name: sleep disorder
Definition: A disease of mental health that involves disruption of sleep patterns.
